        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/synthesis-prior-hemolysis-studies",
        "type": "uofa:Evidence",
        "name": "Synthesis of prior centrifugal pump hemolysis studies",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis aggregating findings from seven independent published studies on CFD-predicted hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps (2008–2023). Covers three distinct pump geometries, multiple turbulence models, and four hemolysis power-law formulations. The synthesis establishes consensus parameter ranges for the Giersiepen-Wurzinger model coefficients and documents the convergence of published RH predictions toward a stable operating-condition ranking. This body of evidence collectively underpins the model-form selection and acceptance-criterion calibration used in the present COU."
      },
